00:12:33,067 --> 00:12:33,867
Cyber libel.

266
00:12:34,500 --> 00:12:38,400
Someone is attacking Felma,
on the FMP website.

267
00:12:39,200 --> 00:12:42,200
Don't we have a Safe Space Act?

268
00:12:43,633 --> 00:12:45,333
Yes. Cyber libel.

269
00:12:45,467 --> 00:12:46,600
Okay, thank you.

270
00:12:47,800 --> 00:12:49,867
The person who uploaded it
anonymously.

271
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:52,267
I wonder who did this.

272
00:12:52,400 --> 00:12:54,467
Only Hazel is capable
of doing that.

273
00:12:55,933 --> 00:12:57,900
Oh my gosh, that witch,

274
00:12:58,033 --> 00:13:00,433
will never leave you alone!

275
00:13:03,233 --> 00:13:04,700
Someone grabbed the video,

276
00:13:04,833 --> 00:13:06,867
and posted it on Friendsbook.

277
00:13:08,067 --> 00:13:11,433
Everybody, put your phones down.

278
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:13,367
Don't watch the video.

279
00:13:14,233 --> 00:13:15,267
Let's enjoy the evening.

280
00:13:15,400 --> 00:13:16,233
Come on.

281
00:13:17,067 --> 00:13:18,700
Dessert, Mom.

282
00:13:19,300 --> 00:13:20,200
Here.

283
00:13:22,300 --> 00:13:23,867
Here you go.

284
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:25,033
Have some cake.

285
00:13:25,633 --> 00:13:26,967
Thank you, sweetie.

286
00:13:30,433 --> 00:13:31,533
Don't worry...

287
00:13:32,533 --> 00:13:33,700
I'll take care of this.

288
00:13:34,800 --> 00:13:35,833
Let's enjoy.

289
00:13:37,233 --> 00:13:40,367
I won't let anything ruin...

290
00:13:41,300 --> 00:13:42,667
our special moment.

291
00:13:49,433 --> 00:13:52,367
Let me sit down and have a look
at your situation.

292
00:13:52,800 --> 00:13:54,867
A husband can be decided.

293
00:13:55,467 --> 00:13:57,733
The father is there permanently.

294
00:13:58,300 --> 00:14:00,033
You and their mom are done,

295
00:14:00,800 --> 00:14:01,667
you're still the dad.

296
00:14:03,033 --> 00:14:04,133
Jessica's there.

297
00:14:04,267 --> 00:14:05,967
There for you.

298
00:14:06,100 --> 00:14:08,900
The kids back home,
don't forget them.

299
00:14:09,900 --> 00:14:12,167
Try and rebuild up
a relationship.

300
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:14,200
It's never too late.

301
00:14:15,567 --> 00:14:17,267
Thank you, Sir Walter.

302
00:14:19,133 --> 00:14:20,400
Help!

303
00:14:21,267 --> 00:14:22,233
Help!

304
00:14:24,467 --> 00:14:26,900
Oh no! Help! Help!

305
00:14:27,033 --> 00:14:29,000
- Help!
- Be quiet or I'll shoot!

306
00:14:29,867 --> 00:14:31,700
Hey! Wait!

307
00:14:46,033 --> 00:14:47,633
We're calling the police!

308
00:14:47,767 --> 00:14:49,333
Stop it!
We're calling the police!

309
00:14:52,567 --> 00:14:53,767
Manuel!

310
00:14:53,900 --> 00:14:54,867
Manuel!

311
00:14:55,000 --> 00:14:55,933
Manuel!

312
00:14:56,067 --> 00:14:58,333
Manuel!

313
00:15:16,900 --> 00:15:18,400
Hello? Sir Walter?

314
00:15:22,267 --> 00:15:22,767
What?

315
00:15:29,500 --> 00:15:30,400
Coleen!

316
00:15:30,767 --> 00:15:32,333
Coleen, please!

317
00:15:32,467 --> 00:15:33,767
Coleen, wait!

318
00:15:33,900 --> 00:15:35,000
Friend.

319
00:15:35,400 --> 00:15:37,233
We need to go back there.

320
00:15:37,367 --> 00:15:38,400
Just don't pay attention

321
00:15:38,533 --> 00:15:41,900
to our classmates who are
bashing and bullying you.

322
00:15:42,033 --> 00:15:43,233
Don't pay attention to them?

323
00:15:44,000 --> 00:15:47,200
What if your mom gets bashed
and bullied?

324
00:15:47,333 --> 00:15:49,467
Don't you know
how painful that is?

325
00:15:49,900 --> 00:15:51,500
Having them throw shade at you?

326
00:15:51,767 --> 00:15:53,233
Gossiping about you?

327
00:15:53,700 --> 00:15:56,400
Then... let's tell
the teacher about them.

328
00:15:56,533 --> 00:15:57,633
For what?

329
00:15:58,433 --> 00:16:00,267
So they can pick on me
even more?

330
00:16:02,400 --> 00:16:03,633
Friend.

331
00:16:08,267 --> 00:16:09,233
Sorry, friend...

332
00:16:12,000 --> 00:16:13,900
I took my anger out on you.

333
00:16:14,900 --> 00:16:18,233
It's okay, I understand.

334
00:16:19,433 --> 00:16:20,567
Go on,
you should head back there.

335
00:16:21,567 --> 00:16:23,967
I'm going home, Just call me if
we have homework.

336
00:16:25,533 --> 00:16:27,033
All right then.

337
00:16:27,167 --> 00:16:28,233
Okay.

338
00:16:55,267 --> 00:16:57,267
A lot of people
are still commenting.

339
00:16:58,033 --> 00:16:59,533
Please, stop.

340
00:17:01,500 --> 00:17:02,633
This is all your fault!

341
00:17:49,700 --> 00:17:50,867
Right?

342
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:52,467
You're famous now!

343
00:17:52,600 --> 00:17:55,067
You're trending,
hashtag Felma the flirt.

344
00:17:56,167 --> 00:17:57,933
Who's the loser now?

345
00:18:16,467 --> 00:18:17,633
Wait a minute...

346
00:18:18,700 --> 00:18:20,767
who's Paz Antonio?

347
00:18:20,900 --> 00:18:22,533
What a meddler!

348
00:18:22,700 --> 00:18:24,867
And you have to call out
my name.

349
00:18:25,000 --> 00:18:26,333
You want to be famous, too?

350
00:18:26,467 --> 00:18:28,267
Fine, bring it on.

351
00:18:29,633 --> 00:18:31,400
Hazel! Hazel!

352
00:18:31,533 --> 00:18:33,667
- Oh? Oh?
- Hazel, friend.

353
00:18:33,800 --> 00:18:35,500
Hazel, sis, I've been looking
all over for you.

354
00:18:35,633 --> 00:18:36,700
What's going on?

355
00:18:37,167 --> 00:18:38,467
It's Manuel.

356
00:18:38,733 --> 00:18:40,000
They took him to the ER!

357
00:18:40,133 --> 00:18:41,333
He was shot.

358
00:18:41,467 --> 00:18:42,633
- What?
- Yes.

359
00:18:42,767 --> 00:18:44,767
Friend, Hazel! wait!

360
00:18:54,633 --> 00:18:56,133
Friend, Hazel, stay here.

361
00:18:57,067 --> 00:18:57,967
What?

362
00:18:58,100 --> 00:18:59,967
I'm his wife. I need to see him.

363
00:19:00,100 --> 00:19:01,333
Friend, you have to wait here.

364
00:19:01,567 --> 00:19:03,967
You know that we have protocol
in this situation, right?

365
00:19:04,100 --> 00:19:06,433
- No, I need to know...
- Sir Walter, Ma'am Yvonne,

366
00:19:06,567 --> 00:19:07,767
what happened to my dad?

367
00:19:08,567 --> 00:19:09,667
Jessica?

368
00:19:10,033 --> 00:19:12,200
Mom, Aunt Alice.
How's Dad?

369
00:19:14,033 --> 00:19:16,100
We don't know yet.

370
00:19:16,700 --> 00:19:18,567
Jessica, who are they?

371
00:19:18,833 --> 00:19:19,733
Do you know them?

372
00:19:20,700 --> 00:19:21,500
I'm Walter.

373
00:19:21,633 --> 00:19:23,000
This is my wife Yvonne.

374
00:19:23,467 --> 00:19:25,633
And Manuel has been staying
with us for a while.

375
00:19:26,367 --> 00:19:27,700
What happened to my husband?

376
00:19:27,833 --> 00:19:29,400
We're very sorry, dear.

377
00:19:29,567 --> 00:19:31,567
Manuel saved us from a burglar.

378
00:19:31,700 --> 00:19:33,867
That's why he got shot
in the back.

379
00:19:35,300 --> 00:19:36,400
What?

380
00:19:37,333 --> 00:19:38,400
Oh, no!

381
00:19:39,267 --> 00:19:40,767
So it's your fault?

382
00:19:41,133 --> 00:19:43,033
That my husband's fighting
for his life?

383
00:19:43,167 --> 00:19:45,367
Sis, please, don't make a scene.

384
00:19:45,500 --> 00:19:46,367
Why not?

385
00:19:46,500 --> 00:19:47,900
You heard what they said!
It came..

386
00:19:48,033 --> 00:19:49,967
Mom, Mom, please don't take it
out on them.

387
00:19:50,100 --> 00:19:51,667
Why not?

388
00:19:51,800 --> 00:19:53,267
It's all their fault.

389
00:19:53,833 --> 00:19:56,267
We understand your frustration.

390
00:19:56,400 --> 00:19:58,133
And we're really very sorry.

391
00:19:58,933 --> 00:20:01,367
But we did not want this
to happen either.

392
00:20:01,500 --> 00:20:03,633
Will your sorry
save my husband's life?

393
00:20:04,233 --> 00:20:05,400
- Mom. Mom.
- No.

394
00:20:05,533 --> 00:20:08,467
But we're forever grateful
for what Manuel did to us.

395
00:20:08,600 --> 00:20:10,033
He saved our lives.

396
00:20:10,500 --> 00:20:12,133
And we'd be very happy
to offer

397
00:20:12,267 --> 00:20:14,500
any financial assistance
if you need it.

398
00:20:14,633 --> 00:20:17,033
Well, that's the least
that you can do.

399
00:20:17,167 --> 00:20:18,167
Mom.

400
00:20:20,400 --> 00:20:22,133
How badly hurt was my dad?

401
00:20:22,267 --> 00:20:23,467
Was he conscious?

402
00:20:23,600 --> 00:20:24,600
Where was he shot?

403
00:20:24,733 --> 00:20:26,300
He got shot in the back.

404
00:20:27,900 --> 00:20:28,833
Mom.

405
00:20:29,667 --> 00:20:32,033
Mom, Dad will be okay, right?

406
00:20:34,300 --> 00:20:35,100
Mom.

407
00:20:36,100 --> 00:20:38,267
He will survive this, right?

408
00:20:42,233 --> 00:20:43,533
Let's just pray.

409
00:20:44,933 --> 00:20:47,067
Let's pray for him, okay?

410
00:20:49,000 --> 00:20:49,800
Mom.

411
00:20:58,667 --> 00:21:00,300
Thank you for informing me.

412
00:21:00,600 --> 00:21:01,333
Yes, Ma'am.

413
00:21:02,067 --> 00:21:05,367
I will talk to Coleen later.

414
00:21:05,500 --> 00:21:07,200
I'm sorry about that.

415
00:21:07,867 --> 00:21:08,600
Okay, bye.

416
00:21:12,133 --> 00:21:18,233
If it's only me, I can handle
the bashing on social media.

417
00:21:19,100 --> 00:21:21,200
But if it will affect my family,

418
00:21:21,333 --> 00:21:24,067
like what happened to Coleen,
I can't just sit still.

419
00:21:24,500 --> 00:21:26,500
Mom, Do you want me to go
to Coleen's school?

420
00:21:26,633 --> 00:21:28,233
I will talk to those bullies.

421
00:21:28,367 --> 00:21:29,500
I will let them know,

422
00:21:29,633 --> 00:21:31,233
that you are not a mistress
and will never be one!

423
00:21:31,600 --> 00:21:33,267
Let's not stir up more trouble!

424
00:21:33,600 --> 00:21:34,833
What are you going to do?

425
00:21:35,133 --> 00:21:37,200
Are you going
to bully her classmates?

426
00:21:37,733 --> 00:21:39,433
So you'll be one of them!

427
00:21:40,100 --> 00:21:40,900
My gosh.

428
00:21:42,067 --> 00:21:44,300
It will make her not want
to go to school.

429
00:21:44,667 --> 00:21:46,100
Because of the humiliation.

430
00:21:50,033 --> 00:21:52,100
You know what, Jeffrey,
your mom is right

431
00:21:52,533 --> 00:21:53,567
And don't worry...

432
00:21:54,067 --> 00:21:56,233
my lawyers are working
on this case...

433
00:21:56,367 --> 00:21:59,833
so that anyone who shares the
video will be punished.

434
00:22:00,933 --> 00:22:04,533
We're coordinating
with PBI Cybercrime Division.

435
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:06,267
Sis, excuse me.

436
00:22:06,400 --> 00:22:07,367
What is it?

437
00:22:07,500 --> 00:22:10,300
My gosh! I caught our staff.

438
00:22:10,433 --> 00:22:13,233
They're talking about
your viral videos and memes,

439
00:22:13,367 --> 00:22:14,100
on FriendsBook.

440
00:22:14,233 --> 00:22:16,867
So I scolded all of them!

441
00:22:17,033 --> 00:22:18,267
- What?
- What memes?

442
00:22:18,400 --> 00:22:20,433
Oh my gosh, look.
You know what I'm saying?

443
00:22:20,567 --> 00:22:22,900
They even use the video,

444
00:22:23,033 --> 00:22:24,733
and made it stimulating.

445
00:22:25,967 --> 00:22:27,633
<i> I'm not a mistress!</i>

446
00:22:27,767 --> 00:22:29,033
<i> You're a mistress!</i>

447
00:22:32,700 --> 00:22:35,167
Social media is getting out of
hand.

448
00:22:36,133 --> 00:22:37,533
What are we going to do?

449
00:22:37,667 --> 00:22:40,933
They're making fun
of other people's disgrace.

450
00:22:42,400 --> 00:22:46,567
But sis, you have to admit,
you're still gorgeous.

451
00:22:46,700 --> 00:22:48,000
That's right, Noah.

452
00:22:48,133 --> 00:22:50,733
You should hold on tight to her!

453
00:22:50,900 --> 00:22:51,867
There!

454
00:22:52,000 --> 00:22:53,800
You never know, someone might
try to pursue her.

455
00:22:53,933 --> 00:22:56,433
You never know, your engagement
might get cancelled.

456
00:22:58,100 --> 00:22:59,333
Knock on wood.

457
00:22:59,467 --> 00:23:00,700
I can't let that happen.

458
00:23:00,833 --> 00:23:02,767
I won't let that slide.

459
00:23:03,833 --> 00:23:05,500
And now you're going viral.

460
00:23:05,633 --> 00:23:06,933
You're trending.

461
00:23:07,067 --> 00:23:08,000
And then you'll become a star.

462
00:23:08,133 --> 00:23:09,467
That's where this is going.

463
00:23:09,600 --> 00:23:10,767
You become an artist.

464
00:23:10,900 --> 00:23:12,567
Knock it off.

465
00:23:12,700 --> 00:23:17,600
But thank you,
for helping me stay strong.

466
00:23:17,733 --> 00:23:19,133
Do I look okay in that video?

467
00:23:20,400 --> 00:23:21,967
Promise, sis, don't worry.

468
00:23:22,133 --> 00:23:24,200
We are your Felma Brigade!

469
00:23:24,333 --> 00:23:26,900
Or perhaps the Felma Warriors!

470
00:23:27,033 --> 00:23:28,800
- Felma Warrior?
- Yes, promise,

471
00:23:28,933 --> 00:23:30,367
I'm going back there
to scold them again.

472
00:23:49,233 --> 00:23:50,333
Okay, officer.

473
00:23:50,467 --> 00:23:52,200
We'll be on our way.

474
00:23:52,533 --> 00:23:54,133
Thank you.
Good bye.

475
00:23:57,333 --> 00:23:59,400
The burglar is in custody
and will be on our way

476
00:23:59,533 --> 00:24:02,267
to the police station
to identify the suspect.

477
00:24:03,033 --> 00:24:06,433
Jessica, please update us
on Manuel's condition.

478
00:24:09,667 --> 00:24:11,767
Oh, I almost forgot.

479
00:24:11,900 --> 00:24:13,300
Manuel dropped this.

480
00:24:14,000 --> 00:24:15,033
Thank you.

481
00:24:21,100 --> 00:24:22,667
- Let's go.
- Bye, Jessica.

482
00:24:22,800 --> 00:24:23,800
Bye.

483
00:24:38,100 --> 00:24:39,267
Hello?

484
00:24:40,833 --> 00:24:41,867
<i> Hello?</i>

485
00:24:42,867 --> 00:24:44,333
This won't take long,
don't worry.

486
00:24:44,467 --> 00:24:46,733
I just want to tell you that
I know that your monstrous,

487
00:24:46,867 --> 00:24:49,567
home wrecker wife
uploaded my mom's video.

488
00:24:49,700 --> 00:24:51,567
<i> You guys are really something!</i>

489
00:24:51,700 --> 00:24:53,433
Have a little sympathy
for my mom!

490
00:24:53,567 --> 00:24:55,533
Have some sympathy for us!

491
00:24:55,667 --> 00:24:56,800
We're living
a peaceful life now.

492
00:24:56,933 --> 00:24:58,900
Can you just leave us alone?

493
00:24:59,567 --> 00:25:02,000
<i>We've lived our lives
without you for a long time.</i>

494
00:25:02,167 --> 00:25:03,700
<i> For so many years.</i>

495
00:25:03,833 --> 00:25:05,467
So we're going to continue
living our lives without you,

496
00:25:05,600 --> 00:25:06,433
it's okay!

497
00:25:06,567 --> 00:25:08,433
You can stay
with your worthless family!

498
00:25:08,567 --> 00:25:10,100
You can all rot in hell!

499
00:25:11,700 --> 00:25:12,100
Hello?

500
00:25:15,867 --> 00:25:18,233
Excuse me, but please
watch your words.

501
00:25:18,767 --> 00:25:21,733
Being hurt doesn't give you
the right to disrespect others.

502
00:25:22,400 --> 00:25:23,933
And please, for Dad's sake,

503
00:25:24,067 --> 00:25:26,200
we don't need negativity
right now.

504
00:25:28,000 --> 00:25:30,233
I don't care about your dad.

505
00:25:30,767 --> 00:25:33,700
And please, tell your good
for nothing mother,

506
00:25:33,833 --> 00:25:35,833
that she disrespected
my family first,

507
00:25:36,000 --> 00:25:37,033
when she stole my father.

508
00:25:38,433 --> 00:25:39,667
Listen carefully.

509
00:25:39,900 --> 00:25:42,700
If she doesn't stop
pestering mine,

510
00:25:42,967 --> 00:25:46,300
then I will not stop
until I destroy her.

511
00:25:49,200 --> 00:25:50,033
Hello?

512
00:25:51,267 --> 00:25:52,067
Hello!

513
00:25:53,267 --> 00:25:54,667
I said answer me!

514
00:25:56,900 --> 00:25:58,167
Please keep quiet.

515
00:26:09,800 --> 00:26:12,167
You know what I think about
what happened to you?

516
00:26:12,500 --> 00:26:16,567
I think it's Karma.
Because you left me.

517
00:26:17,033 --> 00:26:17,833
Is that your phone?

518
00:26:17,967 --> 00:26:20,833
I think
it's Ma'am Andrea's phone.

519
00:26:20,967 --> 00:26:22,033
<i> Hello, Manuel.</i>

520
00:26:22,667 --> 00:26:23,433
<i> Hello.</i>

521
00:26:24,267 --> 00:26:25,967
Is this Miss Felma?

522
00:26:26,100 --> 00:26:27,033
Who's this?

523
00:26:27,300 --> 00:26:28,567
This is Jessica.

524
00:26:28,833 --> 00:26:30,367
<i> Daughter of Manuel Cruz.</i>

525
00:26:30,633 --> 00:26:33,000
Please, I hope
she won't involve Dad

526
00:26:33,133 --> 00:26:34,367
on her anger towards Mom.

527
00:26:34,967 --> 00:26:35,800
What?

528
00:26:35,933 --> 00:26:37,867
We had a family emergency.

529
00:26:38,433 --> 00:26:39,933
My dad got shot.
